@node Overview "Overview of CybViewBMP"

CybViewBMP is a a viewer of bitmap (.bmp) files that is intented to work with the @{"CyberGraphics" link CyberGfx} RTG system for the Amiga.  It is rather limited in its range of abilities, as it has been developed primarily for viewing files created by '@{"SMan" link SMan}', although it is also capable of loading and viewing any uncompressed bmp file.  Of course, it has limitations other than just its inability to deal with compressed files, and only works on bmp files if you have a 3rd party graphics card, a Workbench with a sufficient depth (this assumes you are running AmigaDOS 3.x), and the CyberGraphics system.

@endnode

@node Using "Using CybViewBMP"
CybViewBMP can be run only from the CLI, as I didn't want to bother creating 'ListView' windows for use with it.  CybViewBMP should be placed in a directory for which a path has been added.  I place my copy of CybViewBMP in my bin: directory. The syntax is simple.  Simply enter CybViewBMP FileName.  If CybViewBMP can't find the file, or the file named is not a compatible bmp file, it will leave a message on the CLI, and terminate.
Of course, termination is accomplished with the close gadget on the window.
Additional limitations are as follows:

1)  Won't work on compressed bmp files.
2)  Will never work on other file formats.  This is a bmp only viewer.
3)  Requires a Workbench depth of 8 bits to work with 8 or fewer bit files, and 16 or 24 bits to work with 8, 16, or 24 bit files.
4)  When the Workbench is only 8 bits, the palette is changed during viewing of the file, and restored when the window of the viewer is closed.
5)  Window size of the viewing window will not exceed the size of the Workbench screen, and if the image to be loaded is too large, some of it will not be displayed.

@endnode


